column49: I have been a teacher and ordering from scholastic for 33 years. The way the site is set up now with a parent order and a teacher order is much more complicated than it used to be and makes it very difficult to order. After some great frustration and phone calls with a previous order to find out where my book of the week order went, I finally figured out it was going to the parent section of my account (which at that time I didn't even realize there were now two sections). I called to find out where my book of the week additions were in the order form (not realizing they were going to the parent section instead of the teacher section). The customer service people said they didn't know. Now I know. This is dumb because I don't want them to go there and they automatically go there. The account or site needs to go back to how it used to be. Only a teacher account for me. It took way longer that necessary to figure out how to place the order.

column49: I had an issue with an order I didn't receive . After a chat and calling customer service, I was transferred to Accounts receivable and finally was able to resolve the issue (my order was shipped to an incorrect location and had an incorrect billing amount.) Amy Hocter and Rita Kroll were helpful, kind and courteous and resolved my issue as quickly as possible. I paid a past due balance while on the website and am now expecting a credit to my account which should leave me with a credit of $14.00 on my account. My account currently still shows a balance of $35.50 owed which is incorrect.
